## SECTION 2 — Shell Operators

| Operator | What it does | Example |
|---|---|---|
| `&` | Run command in background | `long_command &` |
| `&&` | Run second command only if first succeeds | `cd inhere && ls` |
| `>` | Redirect output — overwrites existing file | `cat file.txt > output.txt` |
| `>>` | Redirect output — APPENDS, doesn't overwrite | `cat file.txt >> output.txt` |
| `!` | NOT — negates the next condition | `! -executable` |
| `\|` | Pipe — send output of one command into another | `cat file.txt \| grep "password"` |

