## SECTION 3 — Hidden Files & Permissions

### How Hidden Files Work
- Files starting with `.` are hidden on Linux
- `ls` won't show them
- `ls -a` reveals them
- Example: `.bashrc`, `.profile`, `...Hiding-From-You`

### File Permissions Basics
*(Add more here as you learn — Day 10 of the plan covers this deeply)*
- `executable` = can be run as a program
- `readable` = can be opened and read
- `writable` = can be modified

