## SECTION 7 — Vocabulary Bank

*(Add every new term here in your own words)*

| Term | Plain-English definition |
|---|---|
| Binary file | A file that isn't plain text — images, executables, compiled code |
| ASCII text | Plain human-readable text |
| Executable | A file the system can run as a program |
| Hidden file | Any file starting with `.` on Linux — invisible to `ls` |
| Flag | An option you add to a command to modify its behavior (e.g., `-a`, `-l`) |
| Argument | The input you give a command to work on (e.g., a filename or path) |

